these kind of flip over
using CSS transforms.

6
00:00:18.688 --> 00:00:21.624
So we're gonna need to set a few
things up to make that work.

7
00:00:21.624 --> 00:00:29.223
The first thing we need to do is we need
to add some perspective on our grid.

8
00:00:29.223 --> 00:00:32.146
And there's CSS property
called perspective,

9
00:00:32.146 --> 00:00:36.360
we're gonna give it a value of 100 vw,
it doesn't really matter.

10
00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:39.979
It just affects how severe
the distortion is when things

11
00:00:39.979 --> 00:00:42.678
are flipping over using CSS transforms.

12
00:00:45.299 --> 00:00:47.124
And then inside our square component,

13
00:00:47.124 --> 00:00:50.391
I'm just gonna close all of the junk
up here cuz I don't need anymore.

14
00:00:54.412 --> 00:01:00.782
We're gonna add some CSS transforms that
simulate the card being flipped around.

15
00:01:08.895 --> 00:01:12.019
In order to see the flip happen,
we're gonna need to add a transition.

16
00:01:15.190 --> 00:01:20.454
Let's do something like that, transition
the transform property for 0.4 seconds.

17
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:32.075
So far nothing's happening,
and I think that's because

18
00:01:32.075 --> 00:01:36.743
we need to add a transform
style on here of preserve-3d

19
00:01:41.196 --> 00:01:44.528
CSS transforms especially
when we're dealing with 3D,

20
00:01:44.528 --> 00:01:48.948
is the kind of stuff that I have to look
at NDN at each time, I can never remember

21
00:01:48.948 --> 00:01:54.041
how to get it right, Clearly,
I haven't got it right at this point.

22
00:02:02.901 --> 00:02:05.884
It's because we're applying the transform
only to the button instead of to

23
00:02:05.884 --> 00:02:07.058
the entire flipped element.

24
00:02:07.058 --> 00:02:12.841
So we're gonna change that selector so
that we're targeting flipped and

25
00:02:12.841 --> 00:02:16.301
you'll see that cow flipped around there.

26
00:02:16.301 --> 00:02:21.446
Okay, so it's starting to look
a little bit like what we want except

27
00:02:21.446 --> 00:02:26.433
that the emojis shouldn't be
visible until the card is flipped.

28
00:02:26.433 --> 00:02:31.240
So to make that work,
we need to have a default

29
00:02:31.240 --> 00:02:36.694
transform on the image of rotateY(180deg).

30
00:02:36.694 --> 00:02:40.859
And we also need to add a property
called backface visibility,

31
00:02:40.859 --> 00:02:42.516
which should be hidden.

32
00:02:48.666 --> 00:02:55.150
Okay, so now the emoji is not
visible until the card is flipped.

33
00:02:55.150 --> 00:02:58.795
One thing that we don't want to happen is
for the button to continue being visible

34
00:02:58.795 --> 00:03:01.912
after we flip, because we don't want
you to be able to click on that.

35
00:03:01.912 --> 00:03:06.722
So the button is also gonna get
a back face visibility hidden.

36
00:03:11.957 --> 00:03:17.091
And that means that the background that
we put in earlier is now showing through.

37
00:03:19.020 --> 00:03:24.365
So let's make that a nicer color.

38
00:03:24.365 --> 00:03:27.450
In fact, we're gonna need to add
another element for that background.

39
00:03:27.450 --> 00:03:34.668
Let's call it div class=background

40
00:03:43.337 --> 00:03:45.548
And just like the image,

41
00:03:45.548 --> 00:03:51.561
that's only gonna become visible
when the card as a whole is flipped

42
