Let's do width 100%, height 100%,

44
00:04:08.558 --> 00:04:12.843
and we'll slap in a position
absolute in there as well.

45
00:04:20.499 --> 00:04:22.382
Okay, things are starting to behave.

46
00:04:22.382 --> 00:04:26.645
But what we're finding is that some
of these cards are still flippable

47
00:04:26.645 --> 00:04:29.546
even though we've already
found those pairs.

48
00:04:29.546 --> 00:04:33.426
So we actually want to remove those.

49
00:04:33.426 --> 00:04:37.723
Or rather we wanna keep them
flipped once they've been found.

50
00:04:37.723 --> 00:04:42.483
So we're gonna keep
the flipped class active when

51
00:04:42.483 --> 00:04:47.936
the square has either been selected or
it's been found.

52
00:04:47.936 --> 00:04:52.996
And do that like that and so
now you can see which cards have

53
00:04:52.996 --> 00:04:58.283
already been found, and
which ones still need to be found.

54
00:04:58.283 --> 00:05:02.810
Okay, we're gonna get rid of
these default ugly button styles.

55
00:05:02.810 --> 00:05:09.506
We're gonna give that a background
of #eee and get rid of the border,

56
00:05:09.506 --> 00:05:15.995
and let's give it a border radius
as well while we're at it of 1em.

57
00:05:15.995 --> 00:05:21.311
Okay, that's starting to look a little bit
like what we had on the published version.

58
00:05:21.311 --> 00:05:26.235
We'll add that border-radius
to the background when

59
00:05:26.235 --> 00:05:28.810
the card is flipped as well.

60
00:05:28.810 --> 00:05:34.039
We're actually going to change
that background to white and

61
00:05:34.039 --> 00:05:40.275
give it a border of, eee.

62
00:05:40.275 --> 00:05:44.092
Let's make that a little bit bigger maybe,
a little bit thicker.

63
00:05:51.844 --> 00:05:55.162
Okay, we're starting to get a little
bit closer to what we had before.

64
